# Journal Q1 Polish (Condensed)

**Purpose:** Final polish pass for Q1 journals. NOT for initial writing.

**Links to:** paper-writing, technical-english-cs, experiment-tracking, internal-critique, publication-strategy

---

## Step 1 — Notation & Complexity Sync

1.1 Notation Table: Map symbols paper ↔ thesis
1.2 Complexity: O(·) with explicit variable definitions
1.3 Cross-Reference: equations, algorithms, complexity claims match

## Step 2 — De-AI / De-translation

2.1 Banned words: delve, leverage, novel, groundbreaking, paradigm, tapestry, furthermore, moreover, cutting-edge, robust, aforementioned, subsequently, comprehensive, innovative, demonstrates, facilitates, enhances, utilizing

2.2 Active voice preferred. Passive OK for standard Methods procedures.

2.3 De-translation: "has the ability to" → "can", "in order to" → "to", "due to the fact that" → "because"

2.4 Sentence length: 15-25 words target, 35 max

## Step 3 — Q1 Results Table

3.1 Mandatory: Method, Metric, Mean ± Std Dev, # Seeds, p-value (if claiming significance)

3.2 Ablation format:
```
| Method     | Accuracy       | Seeds | p-value  |
| Baseline   | 85.2 ± 0.3     | 5     | —        |
| + Module A | 87.1 ± 0.4     | 5     | 0.002*   |
```

3.3 Seed justification: "5 seeds following [citation]"

3.4 Statistical tests: "outperforms" → paired t-test, "comparable" → equivalence test

3.5 Checklist: mean±std for ablation, seed count, p-values, bold best, hardware spec
